trans-unit.source: The Visual Studio Shell enables Visual Studio Partners to build tools and applications on top of the Visual Studio IDE.
trans-unit.target: The Visual Studio Shell enables Visual Studio Partners to build tools and applications on top of the Visual Studio IDE.

trans-unit.source: Using integrated mode, you can release a Visual Studio extension for use by customers who have not installed Visual Studio.
trans-unit.target: Using integrated mode, you can release a Visual Studio extension for use by customers who have not installed Visual Studio.

trans-unit.source: In isolated mode, you can release a custom application that makes use of a subset of Visual Studio IDE features.
trans-unit.target: In isolated mode, you can release a custom application that makes use of a subset of Visual Studio IDE features.

trans-unit.source: The Visual Studio Shell is available for Visual Studio 2015, Visual Studio 2013, Visual Studio 2012, and Visual Studio 2010.
trans-unit.target: The Visual Studio Shell is available for Visual Studio 2015, Visual Studio 2013, Visual Studio 2012, and Visual Studio 2010.

trans-unit.source: It is not available for Visual Studio 2017.
